improving the safety and security

00:34:08.040 --> 00:34:09.340
and correcting software flaws.

00:34:09.340 --> 00:34:11.880 position:56%
So, I would kind of cut it off right

00:34:11.880 --> 00:34:14.570
after the definition
of security testing.

00:34:14.570 --> 00:34:17.660
So in many cases, we
are seeing agencies move

00:34:17.660 --> 00:34:21.240
to protect the other types
of equities that you see

00:34:21.240 --> 00:34:24.660
in the permanent exception,
like privacy, like safety.

00:34:24.660 --> 00:34:30.970
The NHTSA, the Transportation
Security Agency as well as the FTC

00:34:30.970 --> 00:34:36.180
and others like they are already
moving to protect against hacking

00:34:36.180 --> 00:34:37.780
that in a way that violate privacy.

00:34:37.780 --> 00:34:39.700
We've got laws for that.

00:34:39.700 --> 00:34:44.730 position:56%
So it's unclear to us why 1201 ought
to be the vehicle, so to speak,

00:34:44.730 --> 00:34:46.870
to prevent those types
of activities.

00:34:46.870 --> 00:34:51.370
I will also say that when it comes
to trafficking, you know, we--

00:34:51.370 --> 00:34:53.280
because we are a penetration
testing company,

00:34:53.280 --> 00:34:55.650
we actually do use software.

00:34:55.650 --> 00:34:59.210
We even market software that
can be used to circumvent.

00:34:59.210 --> 00:35:02.210
And some of that includes
circumventing passwords

00:35:02.210 --> 00:35:03.660
or brute forcing encryption.

00:35:03.660 --> 00:35:05.920
Companies, this is very valuable
to them because they want

00:35:05.920 --> 00:35:08.130
to know what flaws
they're susceptible to.

00:35:08.130 --> 00:35:10.100
And so, we have to
traffic in that software

00:35:10.100 --> 00:35:12.390
in order to run our business.

00:35:12.390 --> 00:35:13.920
And we work with security
researchers

00:35:13.920 --> 00:35:15.880
that send us updates and exploits.

00:35:15.880 --> 00:35:18.550
They traffic in the
circumvention tools to us

00:35:18.550 --> 00:35:20.300
so that we can keep our
products up to date.

00:35:20.300 --> 00:35:23.760
So this is an important
component of security research.

00:35:23.760 --> 00:35:26.290
And I will just-- I'm saying
this because I wouldn't want

00:35:26.290 --> 00:35:30.050
to see trafficking fall by
the wayside if we're talking

00:35:30.050 --> 00:35:32.680
about reforming the
permanent exemptions.

00:35:32.680 --> 00:35:33.980
&gt;&gt; Kevin Amer: Thank you.

