00:44:37.730 --> 00:44:43.480
to provide user rights in areas
that are part of the Directive.

00:44:43.480 --> 00:44:46.210
Although I don't think it's
really spelled out very clearly.

00:44:46.210 --> 00:44:48.800
And it's not the same as
sort of registering works.

00:44:48.800 --> 00:44:52.840
I think though that the movement
against registration and copyright

00:44:52.840 --> 00:44:57.060
across the board for
everything has been a mistake.

00:44:57.060 --> 00:44:59.930
And I think the idea--
You could make an analogy

00:44:59.930 --> 00:45:03.750
between the collateral damage
and harm that's been done

00:45:03.750 --> 00:45:08.420
by having copyright
always-- I mean, everything--

00:45:08.420 --> 00:45:09.720
&gt;&gt; Kevin Amer: I think we do--

00:45:09.720 --> 00:45:11.940
&gt;&gt; James Love: -- on TPMs, this
