why they may not be advisable.

00:47:49.590 --> 00:47:53.180
But, if you can trust
the encryption exemption

00:47:53.180 --> 00:47:55.360
with a security testing exemption,

00:47:55.360 --> 00:47:57.210
security testing exemption
I think needs to be

00:47:57.210 --> 00:47:59.970
with the authorization
whereas with encryption,

00:47:59.970 --> 00:48:01.350
you just need to make
a good faith effort.

00:48:01.350 --> 00:48:02.780
And I know in the rulemaking,
we heard a lot

00:48:02.780 --> 00:48:06.610
about the bug bounty programs or
front door policy or, you know,

00:48:06.610 --> 00:48:11.230
ways in which there is sort of
an understood protocol or norms

00:48:11.230 --> 00:48:14.590
or ethics that one might go
about in getting authorization.

00:48:14.590 --> 00:48:18.590
If we made some revision to
call it a good faith effort

00:48:18.590 --> 00:48:19.990
to get authorization as opposed

00:48:19.990 --> 00:48:22.370
to a requirement, would
that help you out?

00:48:22.370 --> 00:48:25.220
Would that be-- Do others
see problems with that?

00:48:25.220 --> 00:48:29.030 position:56%
&gt;&gt; Harley Geiger: So, unfortunately,
no, and for a couple of reasons.

00:48:29.030 --> 00:48:31.190
It's definitely better
than a requirement.

00:48:31.190 --> 00:48:34.650 position:56%
And our standard practice is that we
do make a good faith effort to try

00:48:34.650 --> 00:48:38.380
to contact the vendor,
whoever has the flaw.

00:48:38.380 --> 00:48:43.330
And however, that is not--
not every manufacturer,

00:48:43.330 --> 00:48:48.980
not every vendor actually has a
means of being able-- of contact.

00:48:48.980 --> 00:48:52.240
And it is a policy that
in fact, the Department

00:48:52.240 --> 00:48:57.000
of Commerce is working now
to try to get more adopted

00:48:57.000 --> 00:48:58.730
through its multi-stakeholder
process.

00:48:58.730 --> 00:49:01.900
But it is not really the norm
among industries right now.

00:49:01.900 --> 00:49:05.070
And especially with the internet
of things, where we're seeing a lot

00:49:05.070 --> 00:49:09.540
of companies that are
entering this computer space

00:49:09.540 --> 00:49:13.770
and that maybe have not had a
lot of experience in it before,

00:49:13.770 --> 00:49:17.170 position:56%
they don't necessarily think to have
a vulnerability disclosure process.

00:49:17.170 --> 00:49:19.690 position:56%
And sometimes, it is very
difficult to get in touch with them.

00:49:19.690 --> 00:49:20.990
The other problem with it--

00:49:20.990 --> 00:49:22.290
&gt;&gt; Regan Smith: Well, in that case,

00:49:22.290 --> 00:49:24.360
wouldn't you have made
your good faith effort or--

00:49:24.360 --> 00:49:25.660
&gt;&gt; Harley Geiger: The
other problem is

00:49:25.660 --> 00:49:27.850
that you don't always know
how to contact a vendor.

00:49:27.850 --> 00:49:31.160
And some of the research that
we do is entirely online.

00:49:31.160 --> 00:49:32.460
Some of it is automated.

00:49:32.460 --> 00:49:35.650
We have a Project Sonar that
scans the entire Internet

00:49:35.650 --> 00:49:37.360
in fact, does it every week.

00:49:37.360 --> 00:49:41.750
And it is not always
feasible to contact the owner.

00:49:41.750 --> 00:49:44.700
And it's often not
feasible to contact--

00:49:44.700 --> 00:49:48.310
in the case of Project Sonar, where
we're scanning billions of devices,

00:49:48.310 --> 00:49:49.610
there are millions of owners.

00:49:49.610 --> 00:49:51.560
How do you contact all of them?

00:49:51.560 --> 00:49:54.460
So, it's a best a practice
but it is not one

00:49:54.460 --> 00:49:59.070 position:56%
that I think the protection ought to
hinge on because it doesn't scale.

00:49:59.070 --> 00:50:01.250
You know, you don't
always know the owner.

00:50:01.250 --> 00:50:04.200
And even if you do know all
the owners, it doesn't scale

00:50:04.200 --> 00:50:06.480
and it's not always the practice

00:50:06.480 --> 00:50:08.550
of every manufacturer
to have an avenue.

00:50:08.550 --> 00:50:11.620
And so, there is-- we've
experienced it, sometimes dispute

00:50:11.620 --> 00:50:15.230
over whether the effort
was good enough.

